{
  "stem": "19198.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 197.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The-- and for a while, it was very effective.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But then the emigration became-- developed from a trickle into-- into a stream, and the most productive people of the community began to disappear.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in Germany, almost anything, even in-- in a democratic Weimar Republic, the government had a great deal to say about-- about any organized activity.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But from the moment the Nazis came to power, everything had to be approved by the government.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So all these things were approved by the Nazis, but what created them was the spirit of the community.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I am not entirely certain.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- as far as I recall, when I visited there in 1937, the-- I was in the United States on a student visa from 1935 to 1937, then had to go back in order to change that student visa into an immigration visa that gave me the chance to settle here permanently.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For that purpose I went back to Germany in the summer of 1937 during my school vacation, and I spent, I think, about six or seven weeks in-- in Eberbach.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before I left for the United States, my-- the-- at least officially, my German-- my parents still owned and conducted their business.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Still were partners, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] The-- the feeling of the family was that I had definitely made the right decision, because Germany was no place for a Jew to grow up.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And certainly there was very little educational and professional chance, the-- even though the one course that I had chosen [LAUGHS] still was there as long as there would be a sizable Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they agreed fully with my intent to emigrate.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
